AI Poker Trainer App – Core Requirements
1. User Account System
•	Users can sign up, log in, and log out
•	Store user profiles and progress
•	Optional: guest mode
•	 Needed for tracking learning progress and personalization
2. Poker Game Engine
•	Implement core poker logic (e.g., Texas Hold’em):
o	Deck generation & shuffling
o	Dealing cards
o	Betting rounds
o	Hand evaluation (win/loss)
o	This is the foundation of the entire app
3. AI Opponent / Trainer
•	AI that plays poker against the user
•	Adjustable difficulty levels (beginner → advanced)
•	AI makes decisions based on:
o	Hand strength
o	Position
o	Betting patterns
-	Core “trainer” functionality
4. Decision Feedback System
•	After each hand, provide feedback:
o	“Correct play” vs “suboptimal play”
o	Suggested action (fold/call/raise)
•	Show reasoning (basic → advanced explanations)
5. Hand Analysis & Replay
•	Users can:
o	Review previous hands
o	Replay decisions step-by-step
o	See alternative outcomes
o	Critical for learning and improvement
6. Training Modes
•	Multiple modes such as:
o	Practice mode (no pressure)
o	Scenario-based training (e.g., “short stack”)
o	Quiz mode (what should you do here?)
o	Adds structured learning
7. Statistics & Progress Tracking
•	Track:
o	Win rate
o	Decision accuracy
o	Common mistakes
•	Display dashboards/graphs
•	Keeps users engaged + measurable improvement
8. UI/UX Interface (Maybe JavaFX or Swing)
•	Interactive poker table UI
•	Clear display of:
o	Cards
o	Chips
o	Actions
•	Responsive and intuitive design
9. Data Persistence
•	Store:
o	User accounts
o	Game history
o	Statistics
•	Use a database (e.g., SQLite similar to address book project)
10. System Architecture & Modularity
•	Clean separation:
o	Game logic
o	AI logic
o	UI
o	Data layer
•	Use interfaces (e.g., DAO pattern)
